# Case A: CLC Workflow Automation

## Client
Supported Study Hall staff at the Center for Learning and Collaboration (CLC)

## Problem
CLC staff spend hours each week manually logging into individual student Canvas accounts and transcribing assignment data to create to-do lists in Google Docs.

## Goal
Automate data extraction from Canvas LMS and generate a centralized Google Doc or Sheet per student that advisors can reference without manual entry.

## Tech Stack
Python, Canvas LMS API, Google Workspace APIs (Docs, Sheets)

## Team
Developers: Luke Ryan, Jack Weinberg
Club Lead: Cayden Auyang

## Working Rules
- This folder is scoped to Case A only. Do not modify files outside projects/case-a-clc-workflow/ unless explicitly asked.
- Do not commit secrets, API keys, or credentials. Use .env files and add them to .gitignore.
- Follow the club branch naming convention: case-a/short-description (lowercase, hyphens).
- Never push directly to main. All changes go through a Pull Request with at least 1 approval.
- When writing code, prefer clarity over cleverness. These developers are high school students learning collaborative coding.
- If you generate code the developer cannot explain, flag it and summarize what it does in plain English.

## Definition of Done (Phase 1)
A working script that authenticates with the Canvas API and pulls one student's full assignment list into a formatted Google Doc or Sheet.
